body:
I was able to reproduce the issue locally with a simple consumer. Settings the ack-timeout to 1sec and to ack with a random delay that can exceed the threshold. 

Running 2 consumers, the negative `unackedMessages` counters shows up after few minutes.

```java
PulsarClient client = PulsarClient.create("pulsar://localhost:6650");
        ConsumerConfiguration conf = new ConsumerConfiguration();
        conf.setSubscriptionType(SubscriptionType.Shared);
        conf.setAckTimeout(1, TimeUnit.SECONDS);
        Consumer consumer = client.subscribe("persistent://sample/standalone/ns1/my-topic", "my-sub", conf);

        ScheduledExecutorService executor = Executors.newScheduledThreadPool(10);

        Random r = new Random();

        while (true) {
            Message msg = consumer.receive();
            int delayMs = r.nextInt(2000);
            executor.schedule(() -> {
                consumer.acknowledgeAsync(msg);
            }, delayMs, TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS);
        }
```

Still no idea of cause or possible fix.

